                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am a chairman; I went in pursuit of the prisoner, and stopped him at the corner of Quebec-street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18020113-22-person287">Q. </persName>
            (To Ruff.) Where did you place this carpet when you went into the public-house? - A. Upon a rail against the chair-house, close to the door.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I follow portering; a man hired me to carry this carpet; he took me into the very house where these men were, and treated me with part of a pint of porter, and he came out of the house with me; these people came up, and cried, stop thief, and I was frightened, and threw down the carpet. <rs id="t18020113-22-verdict114" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18020113-22-verdict114" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 46.</p>
